    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="631"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/11258</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-27">May 27,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: We understand that a copy of the
                    attached telegram of May 23 from our Minister at Cairo,<note n="21"
                        xml:id="d631fn21">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> which we regard as very important, has
                    been sent to the White House.</p>
                <p>It is our feeling that conversations on the subject between officers of the
                    Department and non-Zionists would have no result, because the latter have no
                    influence with the Zionists. It is not likely that the Zionists can be
                    influenced by anyone except the President himself.</p>
                <p>If you feel like discussing the matter with the President, we shall of course be
                    glad to prepare any additional material which you may desire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
